{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:56:08.873145+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have a clear picture of this issue. Here's my analysis:\n\n**Issue #1** by BruceKZ reports that `AudioSegment.from_file` silently returns an empty `AudioSegment` when given a non-existent file path. However, the reporter **self-resolved** it in an update at the bottom of the issue:\n\n1. The root cause was an **older ffmpeg version (4.2.7)** on their CI — ffmpeg 4.2.7 emits enough output to fool pydub into thinking it got a valid 0-length stream.\n2. Upgrading to **ffmpeg 6.0** fixed the problem — newer ffmpeg properly fails, and pydub correctly raises `CouldntDecodeError`.\n3. The reporter explicitly says \"Closing this from my side — sorry for the noise\" and suggests the only actionable item is a docs note about ffmpeg >= 5.\n\nThere are no comments, no labels, and no linked PRs. The reporter self-triaged the issue as not a pydub bug. I'll close it as not planned with an appreciative comment, and note that a docs contribution would still be welcome.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 678, "prompt_tokens": 9745, "total_tokens": 10423, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 192, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 4608}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "28df7ca3a0294361996af62866dbcb6b", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead86-ba33-7f70-84ec-57faf7f184e6-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "issue_write", "args": {"method": "update", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R02_C03_A01", "issue_number": 1, "state": "closed", "state_reason": "not_planned"}, "id": "call_da6ed271050541c5ae3e16af", "type": "tool_call"}, {"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R02_C03_A01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the thorough report and for following up with your findings, @BruceKZ! Glad you were able to trace it to the older ffmpeg version on your CI.\n\nClosing as not a pydub bug — ffmpeg >= 5 provides the expected failure behavior, and pydub already surfaces the error correctly when ffmpeg reports one.\n\nIf you (or anyone) would like to contribute a small docs PR noting the ffmpeg >= 5 recommendation for predictable error handling, that would be a welcome addition. Thanks again!"}, "id": "call_dc75cac0cfea42768ff38733", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9745, "output_tokens": 678, "total_tokens": 10423, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 4608}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 192}}}}]}}}
